# Firebase Authentication

When changing authentication or user management code, **read and follow [docs/AUTH.md](docs/AUTH.md)**. That document is the source of truth for:

- Domain restriction to `@addisenergy.com` (do not remove or relax).
- Approval flow: registration creates a Firestore pending request; only approved users (custom claim `approved`) can log in.
- Where credentials come from (Streamlit secrets vs env vars); do not hardcode keys.
- Single Firebase Admin SDK initialization; use the existing `auth` module.
- Token handling: ID token in session, verified via `auth.firebase_config.verify_token()` on protected routes.
- Firestore `pending_users` collection schema and approval/reject behavior.

**Key paths:** `auth/firebase_config.py`, `auth/user_management.py`, `frontend/components/auth_components.py`, `scripts/manage_users.py`.
